{"title": "Hypothalamic and hypophyseal regulation of growth hormone secretion", "url": "https://link.springer.com/article/10.1023/A:1022579327647", "author": "MT Bluet-Pajot and J Epelbaum and D Gourdji\u2026", "abstract": "Regulation of pulsatile secretion of growth hormone (GH) relies on hypothalamic neuronal loops, major transmitters involved in their operation are growth hormone releasing hormone (GHRH) synthetized mostly in arcuate nucleus (ARC) neurons, and somatostatin (SRIH) \u2026"}